            <title>[LU-16119] Workaround __write_overflow_field errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16119</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v5.17-rc3-1-gf68f2ff91512&lt;br/&gt;
   fortify: Detect struct member overflows in memcpy() at compile-time&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;memcpy and memset of collections of struct members&lt;br/&gt;
will trigger:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;error: call to &#8216;__write_overflow_field&#8217; declared with attribute&lt;br/&gt;
   warning: detected write beyond size of field (1st parameter);&lt;br/&gt;
   maybe use struct_group()?&lt;br/&gt;
   &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-Werror&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; __write_overflow_field(p_size_field, size);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
